<br>
If it means &quot;there are basic, clear guidelines regarding unacceptable behaviours and the ruleset is tweaked to encourage roleplay interactions&quot; you get one possible scenario.<br>
<br>
If it means &quot;vague or subjective interpretation of what roleplay is, with inconsistent enforcement and alot of perceived bias in said enforcement&quot; you get a whole different possible scenario.<br>
<br>
The two questions are so intimately tied together that you can't answer the question (what would it be like) without answering the premise (define &quot;roleplay&quot; and &quot;enforced&quot;).<br>
<br>
It's like asking what it would be like to live on another planet, without mentioning what planet. Living on Mars would be a whole different thing than a colony on Pluto.<br>
